This street serves the guild and training district, where the @@Gtraining hall@@N to the east provides instruction in martial and practical skills to citizens, militia recruits, and visiting adventurers. The walk is wider than typical residential streets, designed to accommodate the groups of trainees who move between the hall, the equipment vendors, and the barracks on drill days. Practice weapons are sometimes left leaning against building walls by forgetful students, and the cobblestones near the hall entrance are worn smooth by the shuffling footwork of combat drills conducted in the street when the indoor training floor is full. A @@GJade Magistracy notice@@N on the wall lists the current schedule of training sessions and the fees required for public instruction.

