@@GOhn-Sek Training Hall@@N~
The Ohn-Sek Training Hall honors the Iron Hands tradition of House Ohn-Sek, whose mercenary soldiers established the martial discipline that still defines Kowloon's defense doctrine. The hall's interior is a large open floor of packed earth scored with the footwork patterns of a thousand training bouts, ringed by wooden practice dummies and padded striking posts. Weapon racks along the walls hold training versions of every weapon type sold in the city, their edges dulled but their weight true to combat specifications. A raised observation platform at the back of the hall allows instructors to oversee multiple training groups simultaneously. The @@Ggreen pennants@@N of the Wardens of Iron hang from the ceiling beams, their faded fabric a reminder that this hall has produced soldiers and defenders since the generation that followed the Covenant's signing. The air smells of sweat, leather, and the chalk used to improve grip on weapon handles.

