#3750
executioner kowloon~
the Executioner of Kowloon~
The Executioner of Kowloon stands here in iron silence, half-masked face surveying the square.

~
The Executioner is a figure of constitutional authority rather than personal menace, though the distinction offers little comfort to those who face the office's judgment. An iron half-mask forged in the shape of a snarling river dragon conceals the upper face, and the body beneath the formal black coat moves with the controlled economy of someone trained to end resistance quickly and cleanly. No name, no faction, no visible allegiance marks this figure, only the office and the weight of the Covenant's oldest and most absolute promise: final judgment, publicly witnessed, without appeal.

